@page
@model ITWebsite.Pages.PrivacyModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Privacy Policy";
}

<section class="py-5">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-lg-8">

                <h1 class="fw-bold section-title mb-4">Privacy Policy</h1>

                <p class="text-secondary">
                    Effective Date: February 26, 2026
                </p>

                <p>
                    This Privacy Policy describes how Kairos Technologies (operated by James Hsu)
                    collects, uses, and protects personal information in connection with residential IT support services.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">1. Who We Are</h5>
                <p>
                    Kairos Technologies is an independent residential IT support provider based in Calgary, Alberta.
                    Services are provided exclusively to individuals and families.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Privacy-related inquiries may be directed to:
                    <br />
                    James Hsu<br />
                    privacy@kairostech.ca<br />
                    Calgary, Alberta, Canada
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">2. Information We Collect</h5>
                <p>When you contact us or request services, we may collect:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Your name</li>
                    <li>Email address</li>
                    <li>Phone number</li>
                    <li>Description of your technical issue</li>
                    <li>Device or network details you voluntarily provide</li>
                </ul>

                <p>
                    We do not intentionally collect sensitive personal information unless it is necessary
                    to provide the requested service.
                </p>

                <p>
                    We do not collect payment card information through this website.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">3. How We Use Information</h5>
                <p>Personal information is used only to:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Respond to inquiries</li>
                    <li>Provide requested IT services</li>
                    <li>Schedule appointments</li>
                    <li>Communicate regarding your service</li>
                    <li>Issue invoices and maintain basic business records</li>
                </ul>

                <p>
                    We do not sell, rent, or trade personal information.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">4. Contact Form & Communications</h5>
                <p>
                    Messages submitted through the website contact form are delivered to our business email inbox.
                    These communications may be stored for service documentation and record-keeping purposes.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">5. Remote Support Sessions</h5>
                <p>
                    If you authorize remote support, you consent to temporary access to your device
                    for the purpose of completing the requested work.
                </p>
                <p>
                    You may terminate a remote session at any time.
                    Access is limited to what is reasonably necessary to complete the service.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">6. Data Storage & Protection</h5>
                <p>
                    Information may be stored in secure email systems and basic accounting records.
                    Reasonable administrative and technical safeguards are used to protect information.
                </p>
                <p>
                    However, no method of electronic transmission or storage is completely secure,
                    and absolute security cannot be guaranteed.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">7. Third-Party Infrastructure</h5>
                <p>
                    This website may be hosted on third-party infrastructure providers.
                    These providers may process technical data such as IP addresses
                    as part of normal website operation.
                </p>
                <p>
                    Personal information is not shared with third parties except as required by law
                    or when necessary to deliver requested services.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">8. Retention</h5>
                <p>
                    Client records are retained only as long as reasonably necessary for
                    service documentation, accounting, and legal compliance.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">9. Your Rights</h5>
                <p>
                    You may request access to your personal information or request corrections
                    by contacting us directly.
                </p>

                <h5 class="fw-semibold mt-4">10. Changes to This Policy</h5>
                <p>
                    This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically.
                    Updated versions will be posted on this page with a revised effective date.
                </p>

            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>